{{Italic title}}
'''''Shāyast ne-Shāyast''''' ([[Middle Persian|MP]]: "Proper and Improper") is an 8th/9th-century [[Zoroastrian]] [[Middle Persian]] compilation of miscellaneous laws and customs regarding sin and impurity, with other memoranda about ceremonies and religious subjects in general.<ref>http://www.sacred-texts.com/zor/sbe05/sbe0507.htm</ref> The text contains about 13,500 words.

The content of this collection are of a very varied character, but sins and good works, precautions to avoid impurities, details of ceremonies and customs, the [[Mysticism|mystic]] signification of the [[Gathas]], and praise of the sacred beings are the principal subjects discussed.<ref>http://www.farvardyn.com/pahlavi4.php#54</ref>

