'''Taqarub''' is an [[Islamic]] doctrine that advocates cordial relations and peaceful coexistence between [[Muslims]] and non-Muslims. It also encourages the involvement of groups often excluded by traditionalist [[Wahhabis]], such as [[Shi'ites]] or [[feminists]].<ref name="Doran">{{cite journal |last1=Doran |first1=Michael Scott |last2= |first2= |year=2004 |title=The Saudi Paradox |journal=Foreign Affairs |volume=83 |issue=1 |pages=35–51 |publisher=Council on Foreign Relations |doi= 10.2307/20033827|url= }}</ref>

