{{Buddhism-stub}}

The '''''Zomi Baptist Church''''' was established on 1952 at Myanmar. It is a Christians' believing church. Its abbreviation is ZBC. The first chairman of the Zomi Baptist Convention is  Mr.ST.Gou Hau. Mr ST Gou Hau is the first chairman of the constitution and the first general secretary of the Zomi Baptist Church.
The Lai tribe and the Tedim tribe are associates on the ZBC. In 1995 the ZBC was broke into two the [[Chin Baptist Convention]] and Zomi Baptist Church. Then Zomi Baptist Church of Myanmar (ZBCM) in [[Burma]].<ref>
http://www.zogam.org/adoption-name-zomi-Baptist_Church{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Then the Laimi accepted the [[Chin Baptist Convention]]. Then Tedimmi accepted the Zomi Baptist Church.

